{"submission_id":"sub_301e51f829da54d7","run_id":"2026-06-20T20-50-03-648Z_1885472-23e846bc_ingest_meeting-doc-160966","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T22:02:05.167Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:301e51f829da54d7550b27794e8d96a46dcde997516bf64c4f1b42ee946956bb","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_160966","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_capital_improvements_list","label":"Capital Improvements to Transit System","raw_text":"$15 B in Capital Improvements to NY's Transit System: $2 B 20+ station accessibility improvements, $3 B Signal upgrades along the ACBDFM lines, $3 B Second Avenue Subway extension to East Harlem, $1.5 B New railcars, $500 M New electric buses and charging infrastructure, $5 B State of Good Repair projects","payload":{"claim_text":"$15 B in Capital Improvements to NY's Transit System: $2 B 20+ station accessibility improvements; $3 B Signal upgrades along the ACBDFM lines; $3 B Second Avenue Subway extension to East Harlem; $1.5 B New railcars; $500 M New electric buses and charging infrastructure; $5 B State of Good Repair projects","description":"Capital investments funded by congestion pricing revenue"},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_160966","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_160966#p008_c0005","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_160966/blocks.jsonl","page_number":8,"block_id":"p008_c0005","text_sha256":"sha256:25b05e86eaa826d9e6cfe12fed9e25c4620553d34f12c4e2bae33f2e84475949","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_9018184b3e755644","run_id":"2026-06-20T20-50-03-648Z_1885472-23e846bc_ingest_meeting-doc-160966","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T22:02:11.299Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:9018184b3e7556443a8f14d60d6fb3f8ba922e0faf078d0a6a3792561dee5383","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_160966","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_discount_exemption_programs","label":"Six Discount/Exemption Plans","raw_text":"Only Six Types of Discount / Exemptions: 1. Low-Income Discount Plan (LIDP), 2. Individual Disability Exemption Plan (IDEP), 3. Organizational Disability Exemption Plan (ODEP), 4. Emergency Vehicle Exemption Plan (EVEP), 5. Commuter Bus Exemption Plan (CoBEP), 6. Specialized Government-Owned Vehicle Exemption Plan (SGOVEP)","payload":{"claim_text":"Six types of discounts/exemptions available for the Congestion Relief Zone toll: Low-Income Discount Plan (LIDP), Individual Disability Exemption Plan (IDEP), Organizational Disability Exemption Plan (ODEP), Emergency Vehicle Exemption Plan (EVEP), Commuter Bus Exemption Plan (CoBEP), Specialized Government-Owned Vehicle Exemption Plan (SGOVEP)","description":"Discount and exemption programs for CRZ toll"},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_160966","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_160966#p019_c0004","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_160966/blocks.jsonl","page_number":19,"block_id":"p019_c0004","text_sha256":"sha256:515c9582091ff2b04bc143e8a7e10c74221a2c2bfea8f8dfbd4e46af7c7eb897","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_41a29427351982c9","run_id":"2026-06-20T20-50-03-648Z_1885472-23e846bc_ingest_meeting-doc-160966","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T22:02:16.553Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:41a29427351982c9974cf13b14159cbbe004d8a28b702774129bb60c176abf5b","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_160966","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_lidp_terms","label":"Low-Income Discount Plan","raw_text":"Vehicle owners enrolled in the Low-Income Discount Plan (LIDP) receive a 50% discount on the Congestion Relief Zone peak period toll. The discount begins after the first 10 trips in a calendar month. To qualify, vehicle owners must have reported a federal household adjusted gross income for the previous calendar year of no more than $50,000 or be enrolled in a qualifying government assistance program (SNAP, WIC, or TANF).","payload":{"claim_text":"Low-Income Discount Plan (LIDP): 50% discount on CRZ peak period toll after first 10 trips in a calendar month. Income qualification: federal household adjusted gross income of no more than $50,000 or enrollment in SNAP, WIC, or TANF.","description":"Discount plan for low-income vehicle owners"},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_160966","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_160966#p020_c0003","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_160966/blocks.jsonl","page_number":20,"block_id":"p020_c0003","text_sha256":"sha256:d7ccd44023f9934a420c39f63cb91dd61e6a064f6f7f3fc737dc359d4d2999b7","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_e36938589e5c74fa","run_id":"2026-06-20T20-50-03-648Z_1885472-23e846bc_ingest_meeting-doc-160966","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T22:02:23.291Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:e36938589e5c74fa767bb7277461d7d9787d228b259b6691e147a4b7e2618391","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_160966","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_crossing_credits","label":"Crossing Credits for CRZ Toll","raw_text":"A credit on the CRZ toll will be given to vehicles entering during the peak period via one of the four tolled entries: Lincoln Tunnel, Holland Tunnel, Queens-Midtown Tunnel, Hugh L. Carey Tunnel. Up to $3 for Passenger Vehicle, up to $1.50 for Motorcycle, up to $7.20 for Small Trucks & Charter Buses, up to $12 for Large Trucks & Tour Buses.","payload":{"claim_text":"Vehicles entering the CRZ during peak period via Lincoln Tunnel, Holland Tunnel, Queens-Midtown Tunnel, or Hugh L. Carey Tunnel receive a crossing credit with a valid E-ZPass linked to the correct license plate. Credit amounts: Passenger Vehicle up to $3, Motorcycle up to $1.50, Small Trucks & Charter Buses up to $7.20, Large Trucks & Tour Buses up to $12.","description":"CRZ crossing credits for tolled entries"},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_160966","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_160966#p017_c0006","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_160966/blocks.jsonl","page_number":17,"block_id":"p017_c0006","text_sha256":"sha256:1496438572e9fed274cb6f0cf9e91376a7344afb43472d15bcea3189d7b4c6d8","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_fb8cdae813942d84","run_id":"2026-06-20T20-50-03-648Z_1885472-23e846bc_ingest_meeting-doc-160966","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T22:02:30.841Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:fb8cdae813942d84c7b06e939b1aa7b426ccd6c762b11c3d8000bfea3c08d116","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_160966","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_tolling_rules","label":"CRZ Tolling Rules","raw_text":"Tolls charged as vehicles enter the Congestion Relief Zone – not for exiting or staying in the zone. Passenger vehicles & motorcycles are tolled once daily. Peak period runs from 5am to 9pm Mon-Fri, and 9am to 9pm Sat-Sun. Overnight tolls rates are 75% lower.","payload":{"claim_text":"Tolls charged as vehicles enter the Congestion Relief Zone – not for exiting or staying. Passenger vehicles & motorcycles are tolled once daily. Peak period runs from 5am to 9pm Mon-Fri, and 9am to 9pm Sat-Sun. Overnight tolls rates are 75% lower.","description":"Rules for CRZ tolling"},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_160966","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_160966#p014_c0006","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_160966/blocks.jsonl","page_number":14,"block_id":"p014_c0006","text_sha256":"sha256:69d2f9966ae17562c0de692552f8b019fa52a1b0038d9232cec74c6e3d538601","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
{"submission_id":"sub_6b9163ea306b60df","run_id":"2026-06-20T20-50-03-648Z_1885472-23e846bc_ingest_meeting-doc-160966","submitted_at":"2026-06-20T22:02:36.027Z","tool_args_sha256":"sha256:6b9163ea306b60dfa5e724b17678de69f2841a90746d41a1f188bf94adfb7241","schema_version":2,"tool_args":{"source_id":"meeting_doc_160966","observation_kind":"claim","local_observation_id":"claim_congestion_pricing_benefits","label":"Congestion Pricing Benefits","raw_text":"Congestion Pricing Benefits: Less traffic, Faster travel times incl for emergency response, Cleaner air, Safer streets, Better transit","payload":{"claim_text":"Congestion Pricing Benefits: Less traffic, Faster travel times including for emergency response, Cleaner air, Safer streets, Better transit","description":"Expected benefits of congestion pricing"},"evidence_refs":[{"source_id":"meeting_doc_160966","evidence_id":"meeting_doc_160966#p007_c0005","source_path":"raw/sources/meeting_doc_160966/blocks.jsonl","page_number":7,"block_id":"p007_c0005","text_sha256":"sha256:2e16bc695c977febad980e43f992f4ccc31286adf5ef513cf94ad7cea66cb0d1","text_source":"raw_text"}]},"validation":{"state":"accepted","issues":[]}}
